animal.description:
Marmie came from a rescue in Houston TX where there are an abundance of Chihuahuas.  Wanting to give Marmie a better chance at finding her forever home, they turned her over to CRT.Marmie was born 10/1/17 so she is 2 yr 6 mos old.  She weighs 12 lbs.  She is a special needs

 Chi.Marmie has microophthalmia of her left eye (eye is smaller and under developed).  An ophthalmologist in TX believes that Marmie can see out of this eye but her eyes also do not align so Marmie acts like she is always off balance.  She requires drops in her left eye, currently (3) times a day and also an eye lubricant at least (4) times per day.  This will most likely be required for the remainder of her life.If she gets anxious, she will circle.  She will also circle when she goes outside to do her business.  

She has her own dog bed and blanket that will come with her.  She spends a lot of time in the bed and gets anxious when it is not available.  She loves to burrow under the blanket and stay there and will peek her head out when you call her.

  She does not go up steps.  She also does not like hardwood floors.She loves to play and she does go outside.  She gets along great with the other dogs at her foster home. If they get too close, she will growl but doesn’t seem to interact with them otherwise.She is spayed, UTD on shots and on HW preventative.

She is a little special but is a wonderful, loving little girl that is looking for a family of her own.Her adoption fee is $250.00

.If you are interested in the above dog, please do not email us and tell us that you are interested, but submit an adoption application. The link for the application is below.To submit an application go here……chihuahua-rescue.com/adoption-application/An application must be submitted and approved before a meet-n-greet can be scheduled.Your current dogs/cats must be spayed or neutered unless a veterinarian has determined that your current pet(s) should not be fixed due to medical reasons. They must also be up-to-date on shots and on HW preventative.Reference checks and a home visit are required so SE dogs can only be adopted in NC/SC, VA MD and GA.

animal.description:
PLEASE read this BIOGRAPHY CAREFULLY.  It will answer most of your questions about FERGUS and how awesome he is!

House Trained?  Yes
Crate Trained?   Yes
Good on Leash? Yes
Good with other nice dogs?   yes
Good with Adults & Children?  yes

Hello, I am Fergus!
Fergus the friendly. Fierce de-stuffer of fluffy toys and lovingly referred to by foster momma as “Big Sexy”. 
People, let it be known that I’m a dog with swagger! 

Fergus joined YLDR after spending an abysmal amount of time in a shelter - but his spirit remained jolly, and they didn’t give up on him finding a way out. After some decompression time in his foster home, Fergus’s personality began to shine through, and oh what a personality he has. Fergus has the kind of calm, relaxed, debonair self confidence you read about in romance novels. He can also be a complete goofball, prancing from person to person like a debonair show stallion. 
Again... swagger. 

Fergus loves to be with his people. That can be inside cuddling on the couch bingeing on the latest shows. Fergus is oddly fascinated by dolphins on television & loves nature programs. Fergus loves to roll around outside in the yard, or sit with you in the front yard and people watch as the neighborhood goes about their daily life. As long as he’s chillin’ with his humans, he’s delighted.

Fergus is crate trained, house trained, walks politely on a leash & is wonderful with children taking treats gently from even the smallest of hands. Fergus likes to play fetch… but will play tug until your arms get tired and is always game for a walk or a ride in the car. He’s also content should you need to be away, and showers you with affection & kisses when you reappear. 

Fergus would do well in a household with older children, or dog savvy smaller ones. He’s currently in a household with twin 6yr old boys. He can be a 60lb zooming mass of excitement, not always particularly graceful in where he’s going, so smaller children need extra eyes when he’s on the zoom path. Fergus enjoys playing with a few dog friends in the neighborhood, so he may enjoy having a K9 brother or sister. 
Cats are not recommended. 
.


FERGUS  has an estimated DOB of 4/09/18 and is believed to be a 
Lab Retriever/Pitt Bull Terrier mix.  Fergus  weighed 67 pounds.  

If you live in the Greater Metro ATL, GA area and are interested in  adopting FERGUS, please email us at info@youluckydogrescue.org and visit our website to submit an online ADOPTION APPLICATION. - 

ADOPTION APPLICATION:  YOULUCKYDOGRESCUE.ORG

QUESTIONS - yep, we know you got 'em!  Email us at info@youluckydogrescue.org

Our adoption fee is $300 and includes all age appropriate vaccines, spay  or neuter and microchipping.   The breed and age included in this listing is based upon the opinion of a vet that has examined the dog.  We cannot confirm the age of the dog unless the dog was born in the care of the rescue.  We are located in the metro Atlanta area.   We currently do not allow out of state adoptions as a home check is required as part of the adoption process.

LOLA – Great Pyrenees/Shepherd Mix, TriColor, Spayed Female, 71 pounds, DOB: 4/15/2018. 

Meeting sweet Lola is by appointment only. Please call the clinic to schedule a meeting with Julie, Braxton, Meghan or Lucas.

Lola has been working with a trainer and her new family should continue her training. She knows sit, stay, heel and come. Lola is currently using a prong collar and also a bark collar as her training tools. Once adopted, Julie will meet with Lola's new owners to teach them how to work with Lola. This sweetie is a true diamond in the rough and is waiting for an equally special someone to help her shine!

Lola is perfect for an active single person or couple with no children. She is a sweet and sensitive soul who will just need a little time to open up and adjust to a new environment. Lola is dog aggressive and doesn't do well with other pets, and would need to be the only pet in your home. The perfect environment for Lola would be living with an active single person or couple with no children or pets.

Lola is up to date on her vet services, has a negative heartworm test and is spayed and microchipped.  She has so much love to give, and in the right hands will be a great lifetime companion!

Lola can be shy at first around new people and strangers, but as you spend some time getting to know her, you will have a friend for life. She is truly a sweet and special girl ~~ a true diamond in the rough. She just needs someone to take the time to work with her and gain her trust.

Lola has a lot of energy and would love someone who enjoys daily activity -- hiking, walking, running, extended backyard time playing with toys, perhaps even an obstacle course. Lola's super power is climbing. She can be an escape artist and is able to climb fences, so a yard with a tall privacy fence is definitely a necessity for this super dog!! 

Lola enjoys giving hugs, being pet and fussed over, and would love to be the center of your world. She is looking for someone who will love her as much as she loves them, a nice comfy bed to lie on, daily exercise, and a fenced yard with plenty of treats and toys. If this sounds like you, come and meet sweet Lola. Lola's $130 adoption fee includes 6 months of heartworm preventative and 6 months of flea and tick preventative.

Crabapple Knoll Vet Clinic, Alpharetta, GA.  770.475.8272. Monday-Friday 630AM to 9PM, Saturday & Sunday 8AM to 5PM.

animal.description:
*** Piper's adoption fee has been reduced to $100!!!

Well hello there World, I’m Piper! Am I precious or what?! Hard to believe someone could treat me poorly but I was literally dumped in the country with all of my stuff-food bowls, food, crate, leash, etc... Some humans left me to fend for myself and while trying to get water from a creek, I fell in and couldn’t get out. Finally, a hero came along- a human willing to wade into ice cold water and rescue me. A Good Samaritan came to my aid and held me while FPO worked on getting me into my new start at life. I am only around 2 years old and around 60lbs or so. They say I am a Rottweiler mix, which if you are a Rottie lover, you know that means I have a huge loving heart for my people. As typical with my breed, I tend to pick favorites in the home and I forget how big I am when I come to give my kisses and cuddles so I’d be best suited in a home with breed experience. I love car rides, McDonald’s cheese burgers, and gentle ear scratches. I like exploring the backyard so a secure fence is preferred to ensure my safety. Foster mom says I am this thing called “housebroken and crate trained” which is a silly way to say I know where to sleep, pee, and poop and keep a clean house. I am a little jealous with other pets right now so I am really looking for a home where I get to be center of attention. I try to be a tough girl but I’m really just your typical Rottie Softie.

Our adoption fee is $260 for dogs over 5 months of age and includes all vaccinations, spay/neuter, micro chip implantation and registration/transfer, heartworm test and much more. Puppies up to 5 months of age are $275 and this includes all sets of puppy vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchip implantation and registration and more. To adopt, go to www.fosterpetoutreach.org to complete an application.
Please note: Foster Pet Outreach tries to limit our adoptions to an area within approximately 60 miles of Peoria, Illinois.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Aren't I just gorgeous? I am not a good match for active small children - they make me nervous. I am a sweet boy, a bit shy at first. I need the companionship of another dog to bring out my best adorable personality. I love to play with my foster siblings. My favorite game is chasing the water hose. I love water so much, I may end up in the bath tub with you! I am up to date with vaccinations, neutered and microchipped so you can't loose me.

Kane was abandoned by his owner in the backyard when the family moved away. He was abandoned 2 times by the time he was 8 weeks old. He has bit of separation anxiety. he will need TLC but will be the best dog ever once he has gained confidence in your home. Small children are not appropriate for Kane.
He is looking for his forever family. Is that you?
=========================================================
Please contact app@aarfhouston.org for more information about this dog. You can apply online by clicking on Application .
Puppies that are under 4 months old cannot be adopted outside of our Veterinary Service area. Please call for specific locations. Children under 8 years old often are not a good match for our puppies and dogs. In order to protect both, your child and our rescued dogs/puppies from harm, we seldom if ever adopt to families with young children.
Once your application is approved, we will schedule a meet and greet at one of our adoption events. Thank you for considering a rescue! The adoption fee includes vaccinations, Bordetella, de-worming, rabies, spay/neuter and microchip. There is a an additional $12.99 fee for Home Again for a lifetime registration of the microchip.
Puppies cannot be adopted outside of the Houston area until they are spay/neutered after they are 4 months old. It is against the law in the State of Texas for a rescue not to be sterilized so we have to make sure it gets completed and that we have record of it.
NOTE: In our bios, we provide information based on our volunteer's experience with a particular dog; such as temperament, training, and ability to get along with others.
AARF is a 501(c)3 Non Profit, all breed, no kill organization. Our group is always in need of donations in order to continue to give the needed medical care to our rescues. Adoption fees do not begin to cover all of the medical costs. Any donation , no matter how small is a big help and is greatly appreciated. Please help us to continue to help them. Thank you.

animal.description:
Friends to the Forlorn
Adopt-a-BullBreed: Pit Bull Terrier Gender: Male Estimated Date of Birth: April 25, 2015 Size: 75 lbs Location: Powder Springs, GA
RESCUING RUFUS
Rufus, formerly known as Ronald, found himself at Animal Control in a county where they don't adopt pit bulls out to the public - if they are not pulled by a licensed rescue organization, they are euthanized. Rufus has some large calluses on his joints and all his teeth were severely worn down to nubs. He contracted kennel cough and it quickly turned into pneumonia. Lucky for Rufus, a foster stepped up and he got his freedom ride on April 23, 2020. He was very sick and we started treating his kennel cough and pneumonia immediately with antibiotics and nebulizer treatments. Surprisingly enough, Rufus was heartworm negative! It took him a very long time to finally kick his upper respiratory infection, but after being on several antibiotics for several weeks, he's feeling much better.
ABOUT RUFUS
Rufus is a big, amazing guy. He is a laid back kind of guy that would rather be laying around taking a nap instead of chasing a ball. Rufus just wants to hang out with his people and lay on a big, comfy bed. He is gentle and walks well on a leash. Rufus has proved to be great with children and is not suited for a home with cats. This big lug is actually a bit scared of fireworks and thunderstorms too. With a proper introduction, we think he may do well with other dogs too. He seems to be okay, he just needs some extra time to decompress. He is now neutered, down to 1 pill a day and can stroll the neighborhood with the best of them! Rufus is just a massive love buy, a Class-A Cuddler and cannot get enough! Not in an annoying way, but in a syrupy sweet way. He's down for a nap anytime you're ready and snacks are always welcome!
*Please check back for updates on this big, handsome boy!*
Photo Album of Rufus: https://www.facebook.com/pg/FriendsToTheForlornPitbullRescue/photos/?tab=album&album_id=3070213679703444
Our adoption fee is $300. All dogs are current on vaccinations, spayed or neutered, micro-chipped, on heartworm prevention, and are fed top of the line grain-free food.www.savingpitbulls.org

I'm a sweet, older gal that is active and loves to play! Senior is not in my vocabulary. I really enjoy getting affection from humans as much as I love giving it. I love relaxing on a soft bed too and getting belly rubs! I'm great at finding ways to entertain myself with toys, creativity is my specialty. I think you would be quite impressed with the things I come up with. I had knee surgery on both my knees in the past but I'm fully recovered now. Everything works exactly as it should and it's a good thing too because I'm a natural athlete. I love to run and often run laps around the yard.

I can get along with smaller female dogs but might be best as an only dog because I can be pretty selective about who I think is a friend. We can do introductions and see if we are a match. Contact Mayday today to see just how amazing I am!

animal.description:
HELLOOO new family! I am so excited to meet you! I'm gonna have you giggling nonstop because I'm so happy and goofy. I was born without the piece of my brain that helps me balance (*cerebellar hypoplasia), so I wiggle all over the place. Basically I just love to dance funky all the time! I'm probably gonna be famous soon, so you should adopt me before the pup-parazzi finds me and the whole world wants in on this cuteness. And don't worry, I'm not going to get any worse--I just need you to love me as I am: crazy dancer but always happy to see you. Bonus? I'm already crate trained. Just because I'm goofy doesn't mean I don't know how to behave! Contact Mayday if you'd like to meet me and I promise to show you all my moves!

Ali might be good with older children and would do best in a hone without other dogs.

*Cerebellar hypoplasia is a permanent neurological condition that causes permanent balance and coordination issues. Cerebellar hypoplasia causes jerky movements, tremors and generally uncoordinated motion. The animal often falls down and has trouble walking. To manage this condition for your pet, it is vital that you understand your pet's physical limitations. As your pet may have difficulty controlling movement, you may need to assist your pet when eating and drinking. Providing your pet with a safe environment is essential. Due to the imbalance and wide stance, stairs and uneven ground may cause a hazard. A non-slip, flat surface, such as carpeting, is an ideal environment for your pet.*

If you are interested in adopting or fostering, please visit our site at www.maydaypitbullrescue.org or send us an email at info@maydaypitbullrescue.org

animal.description:
Ahoy mates, I'm Captain Wigglesworth! But as my future family, you can call me CW or Wigs or Wiggy for short. I'm pretty rad so I gotta have more than one cool nickname, right?! I have some tremors and I walk a little sloppy but don't you worry, the doc said I'm all good! I was born with cerebellar hypoplasia, which means I'm missing the part of my brain that would help me balance--thus the goofy walk. But it won't get worse and I won't need meds, so how's that for a win?!

My bestie Janey and I go everywhere together, she keeps me balanced. I'm a little shy meeting new people, but Janey helps me feel comfortable. And once I open up, I'm a happy, playful pup! Ready to take us home yet? Talk to Mayday and tell them you want to meet the cutest fella on the block! I get along with other dogs but Janey decides which ones, so also tell my Mayday peeps if we might have siblings at home. We're going to have so much fun together!

Jigs? Waney? Dude N' Tude? No matter what we title this dynamic duo, the key is that Janey and Wigs love being together and we can't bear to separate them. Janey's outgoing personality helps Wigs bridge the gap his shy demeanor can create with humans. And Wigs gives Janey the unfaltering love and companionship she craves, despite her bossy 'tude. They're both a little different and they embrace that, which is something we'd love to see more of in this world.

Check out my buddy Janey's profile to learn more about her!

Captain Wigglesworth has *cerebellar hypoplasia. **Cerebellar hypoplasia is a permanent neurological condition that causes permanent balance and coordination issues. Cerebellar hypoplasia causes jerky movements, tremors and generally uncoordinated motion. The animal often falls down and has trouble walking. To manage this condition for your pet, it is vital that you understand your pet's physical limitations. As your pet may have difficulty controlling movement, you may need to assist your pet when eating and drinking. Providing your pet with a safe environment is essential. Due to the imbalance and wide stance, stairs and uneven ground may cause a hazard. A non-slip, flat surface, such as carpeting, is an ideal environment for your pet.*

If you are interested in adopting or fostering, please check out our site at www.maydaypitbullrescue.org or email us at info@maydaypitbullrescue.org

animal.description:
I'm a happy, goofy, playful and affectionate girl. I love snuggling and belly rubs! I also like to sunbathe outside. I'm mostly mellow, except when I get brief spurts of energy, and then I just want to run around doing zoomies. I may be an older gal, but that doesn't mean I've lost my spunk! My ears and tongue are always doing their own thing. They flop in so many different directions that my facial expressions will always make you laugh and smile. I may take a minute getting to trust you, as humans were not very kind to me previously, but once you have earned my trust, I become an affectionate goofball extraordinaire! I have a solid foundation of obedience which includes; sit, down, down stay, recall, place command, excellent leash manners, and I ride really well in a car. My adopters will receive included follow up training as well as a lifelong best friend. I can be dog selective so I need to be your one and only pup. I would also do best in a home with no young children as their movements can startle me. Being my owner will have some challenges, but they will be well worth the effort of gaining my love and trust! I'm deserving of a loving forever home. Will you be mine? Contact Mayday today to meet me so I can show you how loving I can be!

If you, or someone you know, are interested in adopting or fostering, please visit our site at www.maydaypitbullrescue.org or send us an email at info@maydaypitbullrescue.org

animal.description:
I'm a lover! I love people. Getting and giving attention and affection is my specialty. I'm great with other dogs! I love the outdoors! I was born to sunbathe and play in the dirt. I have my own special way of walking since I have two legs. I can outrun you if i wanted to but I'd much rather have you love on me. Majestic, grace, resilience, affectionate, calm, happy, loving, survivor, and feisty are just some of my descriptors. I am paralyzed from the waist down so I have no control over my bladder or bowels and I dribble a bit when I walk. It's been a while since I tried a diaper, since I love being outside so much, it hasn't been necessary. I was rescued from Saudi Arabia where doctors believed I was hit by a car which left me paralyzed. I was left in the streets to fend for myself while dragging my legs until some kind people took me in and helped me heal. I am now ready to find my forever home where people will love me for how affectionate I am and not judge me based on how I look. I had a rough go of it but my resilience and will to live shine brighter than any diamond or star in the sky. Would you like to be greeted by my warm smile and affectionate gaze everyday when you come home? Email Mayday today!

*As someone who knows Tinkerbell and has witnessed her love in person, I get goosebumps just thinking about how amazing this girl is. Nothing would bring me more happiness than seeing her in a home of her own. She has traveled from across the globe, been through hell and back, and it still amazes me every day how sweet she is. No other creature on this planet gives love like that of a rescued dog.*

If you, or someone you know, are interested in adopting or fostering, please visit our site at www.maydaypitbullrescue.org or send us an email at info@maydaypitbullrescue.org

One of the things he would like most of all, though, is to have a new home to share with adults-only who are okay with his sure-footed confidence and support his somewhat quirky ways.

He'll join you on lovely walks and fun drives in the car, and, afterwards, kick back and relax with a cozy snuggle in your favorite chair.

Full Description: My name is London and I am very devoted once I find my person, and I am very loyal. I can't wait to make a connection with you and be your best friend. Because I can get a little attached, I would appreciate a home where my people will be home often; I get nervous when I'm home alone. I really like to be outside and enjoy going for walks- as long as I'm with you! I can be selective with other dogs and cannot live with children. animal.description:
Do you remember Buddy? We rescued him in 2016 after he was found laying in a ditch on the side of the road. A throw away dog from a dog fighting area. His ears were cut to base, he was emaciated and scared.

Well, Buddy was adopted by his foster parents who love him dearly, but his issues with other animals and their young son has made it clear that he needs another home. Buddy needs a calm household with adults who realize that he has had a horrifying life and cannot handle a lot.

Buddy is about 5 years old, he is healthy now and fully vetted. He is a laid back dog who loves to hang out on the couch with his humans. He is an awesome snuggle bug and loves leisurely walks and laying in the sun. He is a loyal dog whose bright blue eyes will capture your heart.

Buddy needs a low energy home with no other animals and no kids. He has been so abused that he is has sensitivities some places on his body and this is something hard for kids to understand, so they have just never had him with kids for that reason.

Please help us share this sweet boy, after everything he has been through. He deserves his forever home.

Adoption Application: https://rescuinganimalsinneed.org/dog-puppy-adoption-form/

Believe in love at first sight?  Well, I do now!  I'm already head over heels for you!  My name is Oakley and I am a 5 year old, 100lb. of handsome, Shepherd/hound mix fella.  I am a super smartie and know things like sit, shake, hug, and no.  I am also house trained.  Currently, I am working on figuring out this crate training stuff.  I need to be your only dog friend because I do not want to share you with any other doggo!  I also do not want to live in any apartments.  I am pretty good on a leash so we could have so much fun on some good walks or hikes.  For the most part, I am a chill, laid back kinda guy.  I have spurts of super fun playful energy as well which is perfect for playing some fun games together!  Last, but not least, I am a graduate of the Pups for Parole training program where I was a star student.  I would love if my new family could help continue my training so I can continue to be the best companion.  If you have fallen for me, like I have for you, it is time for you to fill out my adoption application!



My adoption fee is $150 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

animal.description:
?Hello! My name is Remi. I am a 2 yo, neutered male, pit mix. I weigh approximately 53 pounds. I was sprung from the shelter and came to my foster home May 6, 2020. I am still adjusting, but I have made some very good gains in just a little over a week. I have become adjusted to my crate and am doing a good job of coming out of it nicely. I am doing a much better job of getting in and out of the car and riding in it. I've got the stairs and the different floor surfaces in the house--no problems there. I love the outdoors and likely have little experience with indoors, but I am learning, and learning fast! The shelter reported no issues between me and other dogs, and I did well with the meet and greet with the resident male in my foster home. I am heart worm positive. The next step for me would be a foster-to-adopt (FTA) home with a nice, completely fenced in, 6-foot fenced back yard. I am a very good boy in the back yard. I do not dig or try to jump the fence, but  I really do like it outdoors. I am a fairly quiet dog. I may bark some at first, but I settle down quickly. My foster mom's neighbors have even commented about what a nice dog I am. I will be starting HW treatment the end of May, 2020. The ideal FTA home will work cooperatively with my current foster  mom to assure that I am transitioned at an appropriate point in my treatment.   

ABOUT PEACE 4 PITS RESCUE:
Please note that we do not have a facility or shelter where you can view adoptables. We are a foster-based rescue in Chicago-land, which means that each dog is placed with a family in the area. This allows us to better understand each dog's individual personalities. 

You must complete an application before you can schedule a meet and greet with each animal. The application can be found here: http://peaceforpits.org/adoptionfoster-application/ or if you prefer a Word version, download it here: https://goo.gl/bKo84P and email it to p4papplications@gmail.com. Our adoption fee is typically $350 for an adult dog, and $400 for a dog under one year. It includes all vetting and spay/neuter.

animal.description: Sassy Sasha is a special girl that over a year ago had some beautiful puppies that all got adopted. Sasha is estimated to be a 3-4 year old girl and currently weighs 60 pounds. We know she needs to shed a few pounds in time for swimsuit season and we are hoping that her new family will take her for the all important daily long walks to help trim her up (and the humans too). She came to us last almost a year ago through another rescue effort and they said she had given birth to her puppies underneath a house. She was a great mother and of course all the puppies got adopted easily leaving poor Sasha behind to wait anxiously for her own home. Critter Cavalry Rescue has stepped forward to help this rescued girl find a home. Now we are posting her plight far and wide. When you talk about personality we have to sayshe is so sweet but yet has some sassiness to her. She loves to get out and run and play with toys. She is used to the crate but would love to just have a cozy bed inside or be beside you. She loves to get in your lap or lay by you. She loves to play with younger dogs but is intimidated by dogs bigger than her. While we think she would be ok with another dog, we always say that the introduction made slowly and carefully is the best approach for her breed. We have videos of her playing with other dogs but if she feels threatened she will let the other dog know to back off. Her foster family adores this girl who has a big heart and a big desire to have her own home soon! Could that be yours? Please contact us at ccrtennessee@gmail.com if you would like to talk further about Sassy Sasha!

animal.description:
Ayune , SEVERE NEGLECTED . Skin over bones , barely survived . There he was . In a high kill shelter waiting till somebody would close his eyes forever . Luckily we were in time and could take him out of that hell . We rushed him to our vet where he received all the medical care . 

EVen now he only weighs 60 pounds . He has to be at least 90 pounds .We can not rush it . We have to prevent bloat but we are known for our extreme make overs . 

Ayune is a 4 year old black shepherd who has a mix in him of dutch shepherd pr malinois . 

He is extreme abused and is very timid . The first moment I saw him , he was just hiding in my arms with a look in his eyes please don't hurt me. It was heartbreaking . He did not leave my side so it was hard to take pictures . 

He is very calm and we are looking for very SERIOUS adopters who wants to give this black pearl a forever home . Who understand what abuse and neglect means and who help him slowly gain his weight . 

Ayune is scared of other dogs and does not like cats. 

He is located in Middle Island . 

He will be a wonderful dog to the right owner who shows him all the love of the world . 

To become an approved adopter you have to fill in the adoption application to find on our website www.a-teameliterescuedogs.com or email us and we send you one .

animal.description:
Sahara is a beautiful 5 year old spayed female who was previously a Pittie Paw Rescue Dog and has had a rough past.  Guardians for the Animals of Ohio Rescue pulled her from Knox Animal Shelter after she was seized from the former Rescue.   

Her foster has this to say about this amazing girl: 

I know of multiple homes she was in and they didn’t give her a chance, didn’t work with her and didn’t devote enough time to her. She’s had urine burns at one point, dog fights at another, close to being euthanized at the shelter and she’s just been all around let down. She is one of the best girls ever, for most people. She does occasionally leash bite but with a constant reminder and harnesses, she has the potential to do really well. She is fairly calm on her own, she doesn’t approve of being in a crate but can be left out unattended if needed. We prefer to house her in a heavy duty crate.

She does have potential to be with another dog with very slow, steady intros but due to multiple attack’s in the past.. she’s slow to trust other dogs. She is really good with cats and absolutely adores children. She can go for walks without reacting to other dogs but enjoys her person overall. She is house trained and a complete cuddle expert.....she will never let you down with company for a night in. She’s been let down so many times in the past and it shocks me how when she’s truly a good girl. She knows multiple commands and is eager to learn more. She’s very treat motivated as well.

She is really just looking for her forever place to crash, with someone who won’t give up on her.  If interested in more information please contact Guardians for the Animals of Ohio Rescue or fill out an adoption application to meet Sahara.

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please download and complete an Adoption Questionnaire from our website and email Barbara at matisse1600@gmail.com
You can learn about the adoption process and find a Word, PDF and ONLINE version of the questionnaire by visiting: http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/howtoadopt/.
Dog's Name: Scout
Estimated Breed : Collie/Retriever Mix
Approximate Age: 4 years
Approximate Weight: approx. 55 lbs
Currently Living at: Boarding
Adoption Fee: $300
DOG'S DESCRIPTION
Scout is the sweetest butt-head you will ever meet. Scout is very energetic, outgoing, and friendly. He loves to run and a large, fenced backyard would be best for him. He does fine with other dogs if introduced properly and likes to play rough and is dominant, so a non-dominant, playful dog who likes to go all-in on play would be an ideal fit if there is another dog in the home. Scout is very strong and pulls a lot on leash, so will need leash training. He can get rough during play, jumping up and getting mouthy but he is also a super smart dog who would do well with consistent, firm training. He is super sweet with people and will make someone a great dog.
Your new pet will require a refresher in house-training. K-9 Lifesavers strongly recommends all new adopters enroll their new pet into obedience training. This provides for an easier transition into a new home, ensures the dog remains well socialized, and helps form a bond between the dog and the new family.
Adoption fees cover basic vetting, spay/neuter surgery (for dogs over 6 months old), rabies, distemper/parvo vaccinations, treatment for worms, heartworm testing, monthly heartworm prevention and monthly flea/tick prevention (while the animal is in our care), and transport costs from high-kill shelter. Please note that on average, K-9 Lifesavers spend significantly more on each dog than their adoption fee. Adoption fee for HW positive dog also covers heartworm treatment at our partner vets.
Foster Program: Foster homes provide for the temporary care of a rescue until the dog is placed into a loving, forever home. For more information on becoming a foster parent, and our Foster Program, visit http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/foster/ or email our Foster Coordinator at foster@k-9lifesavers.org
Sponsor Me! Make a tax-deductible donation today by visiting us at http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/donate/ . Donations help us offset boarding costs and additional medical treatment for those dogs who need it. K-9 Lifesavers receives NO federal funding and survive with your generous support!
For more information on K-9 Lifesavers, or to view a complete listing of all our Adoptable Dogs, visit our website at www.k-9lifesavers.org.
Please "like" our Facebook Page for the most current events and new dogs.
Thank you for considering a rescue dog!

animal.description:
Tustin T. is an adorable large male German Shepherd Dog (GSD) that was surrendered to a shelter because the owner needed to move out of state and could not bring Tustin. Tustin lived with this same owner in the company of another GSD for most of his life. Tustin's owner attempted to find him a home before surrendering him to the shelter but the home he found had a cat. After a week Tustin was sent back to his owner because he could not ignore the cat. 

Tustin is currently being fostered by a TSGSR volunteer who reports that he is sheer pleasure to live with. Tustin is very gentle, loves to be around people and is housetrained. He loves car rides, sticking his head out the window at slow speeds, and he likes taking short walks. Tustin is on medication for arthritis, so he's not your running companion but he will play a little tug-of-war with encouragement. He's not a picky eater, gently accepts treats, and doesn't beg at the dinner table. Tustin understands, "sit," and "here." If you want a stunningly gorgeous, gentle, well-mannered GSD to snuggle with and keep you company, Tustin is the boy for you. 

Tustin T. Summary:
- Tustin is a Male, 11 yrs old, weighs 90 lbs, shots current, house-trained
- Good with Adults, children, most dogs and travel in the car
- Not well suited to households with Cats & Small Dogs 

When Thulani Senior German Shepherd Rescue (TSGSR) arrived at the shelter to evaluate Tustin he was waiting for us near the shelter play yard. Tustin is an impressive and distinguished-looking dog. We also found him to be very attentive and respectful with us as we began our evaluation tests. While evaluating Tustin we focused on key behavior tests that have been found to be consistent with dogs that are safe in a family home. These tests include a check to see if the dog will guard or protect food or toys from people and a check to see if he will tolerate a full-body feel test that ends up touching most areas of his body (ears, snout, check of his teeth, lifting paws, gently pulling his tail, and much more...). Lastly, we always check to see if the dog can get along with other well-behaved dogs. This check is important since many Thulani Dog adopters already have an existing dog in their home.

At the shelter (and partly shown in the included video), Tustin got along with another large dog. Both dogs were initially excited, as expected, but quickly settled down as they walked along together. Although Tustin did bark a few times both dogs remained relaxed and never showed any signs of aggressive behavior during the meeting. During the full-body feel test, Tustin also did well allowing us to feel most areas of his body without incident...including his mouth and paws. When we were nearing the end of this test he seemed to think that we may have missed a spot and so he flipped over on his back so that we could finish the test by giving him a "belly rub". Good Boy Tustin! His final behavior test checks to assure that he does not guard or protect his food from people. Tustin was offered a high-value bowl of food and as he was eating he consistently let us remove the food before he had finished it without any over-reactions.

Tustin PASSED all the Thulani behavior tests and he has now become a Thulani Dog. 

The shelter did suggest that since Tustin is an extra-large dog that he not be placed in a home with cats, small dogs, or small children to prevent the potential for unintended mishaps.

What's Next for Tustin T.:
Thulani Senior German Shepherd Rescue (TSGSR) will continue to see that Tustin is well cared for and receives all medical care needed for his well being. In addition, TSGSR is beginning a search for an adoptive home that will care for him for the rest of his life. Tustin will come to his new home with a supply of food, a cushy pad if wanted, and other goodies such as toys. 

Tustins medical expenses will be covered for the rest of his life by Thulani Senior German Shepherd Rescue (TSGSR)!

If you want to learn more about Tustin, or are possibly interested in providing an adoptive or foster home, please send us a message by clicking on the "Ask About Me" button. We will often get feedback or "updates" from a dog's foster home and as any updates become available they will be included here.

If you are reading about Tustin on Petfinder.com sometimes an available YouTube video is not listed. If this occurs you can still view the video by pasting its URL into a new browser window or tab.
Available Video URL(s): https://youtu.be/xdgp9JFJK6k

Saving one dog wont change the world. It will change the world for that one dog.

animal.description:
Shiba is a sweet Husky mix, born 10/09/2017. She is a vocal dog who loves to talk. Shiba gets along well with all people and other dogs, but she chases cats. She is playfull and especially enjoys stuffed animals. She is very good about notifying when she needs to go outside. Shiba needs a new home only because she was diagnosed with Addisons, and her former owner was unable to provide needed care. She requires a monthly shot and occasional medication for the rest of her life. Shiba needs an experienced dog owner, preferably one with prior Addisons experience.

The suggested adoption donation for Shiba is $250. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes.

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver.

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months.

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

animal.description: Meet Miss Nola! This 10-year-old, 45-lb Beagle mix found her way to Ewenity after her previous owner passed away. Currently being fostered in Clermont, FL (Lake County), this silly and fun girl is looking for love! She wants nothing more than to be close by her person's side. Did we mention she likes to be RIGHT by your side? This makes walking Miss Nola an absolute dream! Nola loves to chase and catch a ball. She will bring it back to you over and over. In fact, she'll run after any toy you're willing to throw for her! She is crate trained and will wait patiently for you while you're away. This girl is eager to please! Nola is dog friendly and requires a home with a fenced in yard. She is up to date on vaccines, spayed and heartworm negative. As a senior, Nola's standard adoption donation is $250, but $150 for a senior adopter 65+ through our Seniors for Seniors program. Nola wants to give someone her love! Could it be you?

animal.description:
Rinni is a work in progress and probably will be for a while. He was a total mess when he came to us and is improving daily. He may have had mange but was treated at the shelter and here and the vet found no trace of it from his last skin scrape which was at least two months ago. He definitely had yeast and does not do well with  food with chicken in it.  After medication and many medicated baths he actually looks like a dog now and has fur. He had quite an aroma when he first arrived and now just smells like a normal dog. With good nutrition and TLC he has come a long way. Other than terrorizing Sasha and stealing whatever toys she has, his other favorite pastime is eating.  He is very food and treat motivated and cannot contain his excitement. Rinni has a very sweet nature and disposition but because of his exuberance, appetite and size might not be good with small children. We have started the slow kill for his heart worms and will provide all medicine and instructions to the adopter.  If they prefer to do the quicker method we can discuss that with the adopters. If you would like to open up your heart and home to Rinni please fill out an application.

animal.description:
Fiesta is an English Coonhound who is approx. 3 years old and weighs about 50 pounds. She was found as a stray and no one came to claim her. Our guess is that she was a hunting dog who got away from or was turned out by her owner. Right now Fiesta is fearful of new situations and it doesn't seem like she has every lived in a house. Poor girl! She has learned to walk in and out of the house in her foster home and is sleeping in her crate at night. She can walk on a leash now but will jerk and try to run if she gets startled. 

Fiesta will need an adopter who is patient and will love her for what she can become with training and time to adjust. A securely fenced in yard is a must, as she would be almost impossible to catch if she got loose. She absolutely adores other dogs and lives to run and play and romp around in the back yard! Fiesta is charming and engaged once she gets to know you. She would most likely be scared of loud, fast moving children. A quiet home with at least one other playful dog is what will make her happiest! 

We believe that all dogs deserve a safe loving home who wants them. It's clear that Fiesta wasn't valued or well cared for. She is looking for a new family who knows what great companions  hounds can be!


Adoption fee $150.00.  
Included in Adoption: All dogs are spayed/neutered, vaccinated - Da2pp, Bordetella and Rabies, tested for HW/Lyme,  Dewormed and started on HW/Wormer monthly prevention (Interceptor Plus), and treated for flea/tick control (Advantix). Dogs are also micro-chipped and adoption includes lifetime registration. Also included in the adoption is 30 days of Pet First Pet Insurance, and Petco's Free Welcome to the Family Program. This program supports All New Pet Parents and offers Free resources, more than $650 in savings and 24/7 support.

Apply online:
https://www.highlandcountyhumanesociety.org/available-animals/ 

To contact us, please send an email or FB message to:
Email: info@highlandcountyhumanesociety.org
Website: www.highlandcountyhumanesociety.org
FaceBook: www.facebook.com/HighlandHumane

HCHS is 100% foster and volunteer based (no staff, no employees). All animals for adoption are in foster homes and can be seen by appointment suitable to your schedule. Our volunteers may be able to help with local transportation.
Save a life!  ~ADOPT~

animal.description:
Dash is a fun and energetic boy. He is approx 3 years old. Dash just finished his Heartworm treatment and is now ready for his furever home. He needs an experienced person who will work on his obedience training as he will test his boundries. He would do well in an active home where he can exert his energy which in turn makes him a happy boy. He is good with other dogs but would do best as the only male dog in the home. He should go to a home with no small children. 

Dogos are a wonderful breed but we urge anyone interested to dig in and do a lot of research before deciding if they are a good fit for your home. They require a lot of attention and training with them never ends!  Boundaries must be enforced and they often need reminders as they push past boundaires you set! Dogos are loving, kind and gentle but don't mistake that for weakness because they are equally powerful and intense as well! Everyone in the home must be on board with having a dogo and play a major role in their daily routines and training. Yes it is work, but the rewards are ten-fold! Lazy homes don't work for dogos as they need stimulation, exercise, and lots of attention too during their younger years.  Our goal in rescue is to be as transparent as we can about each and every dog plus make sure new families really understand the needs of a dogo!

Dash says you can check out the rest of his profile here::
https://v3.petstablished.com/pets/public/663229?awo=DC+Dogos%2C+Inc&widget=false

animal.description:
Dewey has a split personality.  He can be a friendly, loving dog.  Then there is the Dewey who is object aggressive.  It can be a bone, a toy, a dog house and even a room in a house.
He was adopted to a home with children and another dog.  The dad wanted a jogging partner and Dewey was happy to go jogging with him.  Dewey got along with the family's other dog.  Dewey loved the kids.  Then Dewey decided that the boy's bedroom was his and he began barking and growling when they tried to enter the room.  The mother was the only one able to remove him from the bedroom.  Once out of the room, Dewey went back to being the dog that got along with every one.
With the right person willing to work with his issues, Dewey would make a great pet.
His adoption fee is $100.00.

animal.description:
Please meet Diamond! She is 2 ½ years old, and even though she has already had one litter, she’s been spayed, is current on her vaccines, and is crate trained. We think her mix is Boxer and Staffy, but we aren’t certain about that. What we are certain of is that she’s pretty darn awesome!

In her foster home, Diamond has gotten along great with the animals who live there, including a male dog and a cat. She is incredibly gentle with them. Diamond has been around kids of all ages but prefers older ones (over the age of 10) who know how to be gentle. Ideally, she prefers a quiet household with not much activity, as her favorite activity is curling up on the couch and having her belly scratched!

Diamond isn’t all that big into playing fetch, but with some time she’d probably learn to love it. She does, however, love to play with other dogs! We believe Diamond’s ideal forever home would be one with another dog (preferably male) who she can learn from and who can help her build up her confidence. She would also thrive as the princess of her own palace as well. Having a buddy in her foster home has taken a lot of pressure off her, and she’s proven to be very observant and picks up on things quickly. Diamond has been extremely respectful of the resident dog’s space when he’s not interested in spending time with her; she knows to back off and give him space or find her own space to just chill.

Diamond prefers to nap and chill out on a couch or comfy chair, and loves to cuddle with her humans, but loves to sleep at night in a crate or kennel. It is her safe, protected space. Diamond has proven herself to be well-behaved in the home and doesn’t chew on or scratch any furniture or household items. She will bark though when she’s fearful of someone new coming into or near the home. She’ll need a strong leader in her forever home who can show her that she doesn’t need to be afraid of visitors or even the mailman. With time, patience, and consistency she will trust her caregivers and her new surroundings.

Diamond knows some basic obedience skills, such as sit, stay, and come. Because she’s food motivated and a quick learner, she’ll be fully capable of learning many more skills. She is great at mealtimes (no begging at the table) and sits and waits for her food to be prepared and served, only eating when she’s told it’s “okay”!

Diamond loves walks and seeing the outside world. She is great on-leash and is a very pleasant walking buddy. On hikes in particular, she does very well off-leash, staying close to her companion.

Diamond is a huge cuddle bug once she gets to know and trust her people. If there is a soft space (or even not a soft spot) she will wiggle her way into your lap or perfectly within belly-scratching reach. 

While she is only about 40 pounds, Diamond has a huge heart and the personality of a big dog. Her long tail results in her entire body wiggling whenever she is excited to see you or anyone she loves; it truly is heartwarming to see. 

This young lady is quite the catch and will make a wonderful addition to a couple or a small family who can provide her the patience and time she’ll need to fall in love with you. Don’t worry, it won’t take long! If you think Diamond is the girl you’ve been waiting for, please let us know by submitting an adoption application – https://www.mustluvboxersrescue.com/adopt.

animal.description:
*Please do not inquire until you have read the ENTIRE listing. BONDED PAIR. Not available individually. LOCAL adopters only. No men.*

These two are going to need a very special home, and we hope to keep them together. This is what we shared about them a few days after they arrived with a few edits.

At first, they were terrified. Honeybee didn’t move from her bed for 2 days.  Slowly, but surely, they came out of their shell, and now they are the sweetest lapdogs you’ll ever meet. They still have some timid moments and quirks, but if you’re patient, they will be the best companions ever. We will provide very specific instructions for transitioning them and letting them decompress. PLEASE do not expect a perfect experience on the front end.

Honeybee has a more outgoing personality. She is a busybody and will go around the house to collect your shoes and socks. She will smother you with hugs and kisses if you let her, and likes to burrow in your chest and armpit. ??????

Ladybug is more submissive. She loves being loved, but she usually stands back and observes. She doesn’t meddle and listens well. She loves a good belly rub.

Neither of them have ever had on collars or leashes. We have tried to take them out on leashes several times and they won’t budge. Honeybee has pogo sticks for legs and can clear just about any pen or fence. For this reason, we are requiring their adopters have a fence and NEVER leave them unsupervised. Neither of them like men, but rightfully so, as they were mistreated by a male neighbor. Unfortunately, they cannot go to a home with a full-time male resident. No small children, please. They’re alert dogs, so you can expect barking at strangers. 

We were told they’re a year old. Ladybug looks like a Schnauzer mix and Honeybee looks like a Yorkie mix. They are spayed, vaccinated, current on flea/tick/heartworm prevention and microchipped. They are both heartworm negative. They sleep quietly in a crate together at night and have been using potty pads.

Inbox us to request an application. We are happy to answer any questions you may have as well.

animal.description:
GOOD with dogs, GOOD with kids 10+, NO cats

ADOPTION FEE $400   www.unbreakabull.com/adopt

Hey there world!! My name is Frenchie, and I am 2 years old. I came into the shelter after I was removed from a situation where our living conditions were not very good or safe. I came in with my two girls pups, and they have already been adopted and are doing great, so I am waiting for my turn. I am as sweet as can be, love to go on walks, and I am a champion snuggler. I let you know when I have to go out and go potty, am learning to play, and am learning to just be a dog. I have a lot of energy as I am learning that being a free dog is the most amazing thing in the world, so if you are someone that has an active lifestyle, I am the gal for you!! While I love sitting on the couch and hanging out, I would much rather have some true outdoor exercise time. I do good with kids, but I need them to be older kids because little kids make me nervous. I see them as unpredictable, and so that makes me nervous and I bark at them. I am working at not jumping on people when I greet them. I know that I can get a handle on this, but I’m a work in progress on this. When it comes to cats, I like to chase them. I love to try and catch squirrels and rabbits as well, but I am never successful in catching any of these animals. They are really fast, but because I like to chase them, I was told that my house couldn’t have any cats. Most of all, I am looking forward to just forever being someone’s best friend. If you think that you could be that person that shows me the good life for the rest of my life, head on over and fill out my application to come and meet me!! Until I hear from you, I’m just going to be soaking up the comfy couch for a bit and then asking for a good walk.  See you soon!!! Love, Frenchie (UPDATED 12/09/20)

animal.description:
Hi, it is me... Travis!

Yes, I am adorable…it is true! But I am also difficult.  Are you in interested in adopting me? Please make sure you read the entire dating profile below before inquiring or applying for me.  These humans want what is best for me so they are not going to compromise on finding me my perfect furever home.  

You have probably seen me around here. I have been in boarding school where they worked with me to desensitize me from some previous trauma. I graduated and am ready for a family of my very own.

The humans in my family need to have schedules and routines (believe me… I know what time it is so d not try to lie to me) and yet be kind and patient (Did I tell you, I had a rough start to life?)  I have lots of energy and need walks or runs (I walk or run my foster mom 6-9 miles every day!  After that I have to take her home because she gets tired but I STILL have energy to play) and playtime in a fenced yard (but only if you are out there with me) or in the house every day. I like to push boundaries (no means yes, right?) so I need people who have good discipline and are not afraid to tell me no. I need people who will take the time to get to know me and my specific needs until I trust you.

The furry friends in my family should like to play and above all else will tell me no if I get out of hand.

My furever family:

•will be an all-adult household with no contact with children (living in the house or visiting).
•will not have a cat or any other small creature to stalk and catch.
•will be a Westie (or similar) experienced household.
•will have experience with “difficult” personalities and will follow the guidance of the trainer and rescue.
•will not put me in situations with humans I does not know and trust, such as dog parks or public patios.
•will live within 4 hours of Houston, TX to minimize stress during travel and transition.

* Please note: Travis is safe with us and will stay that way until the right forever home is found. We absolutely will not consider a home in which he will come in contact with children nor one without the required experience.

Travis is 2 years old and has been fully vaccinated, neutered, and microchipped. His adoption donation is $450 which includes 6 months heartworm preventative meds, free microchip registration, and a safety harness.

If you are interested in adopting Travis, please review the adoption process and fill out the application on our website: www.wsrh.com. *** Please describe your experience with dogs with behavioral issues.

All dogs are available until “Adoption Pending” is noted next to their names. WSRH DOES NOT HAVE A PUBLIC SHELTER. ALL OF OUR DOGS ARE FOSTERED IN PRIVATE HOMES. Approved adopters only will be invited to meet the dogs.

animal.description:
Doss is currently in a board and train program and adopter will be asked to work alongside his trainer, which will all be paid for by rescue to help facilitate his transition transition into your home. He needs a home with no children or other animals at this time (other large dogs may be good companions for him with slow and proper introduction). Free training and support will be provided for the remainder of Doss’ life. This is a wonderful opportunity for any experienced handler looking to adopt a loyal companion. 

Doss would thrive with a calm, steady person preferably with breed experience and someone who does not expect to take him "out and about" all the time because he is cautious about and sometimes reactive to the world around him. He is a big, strong dog and needs a handler that can physically control him if necessary.

Doss is attending a Board & Train program where it’s been confirmed that he is an "energy sponge", meaning whatever vibes are happening he is soaking in. He is also hyper aware of distant noises and sights. He needs someone who is willing to work with him and help him relax and keep his mind calm. His new adopters will be expected to implement what he has learned and continue this daily routine in his new home environment. 

The things we continue to work on are: 1. reactivity on leash, mostly towards dogs, occasional humans 2. reactivity in the home to strangers and the energy of other dogs and people and 3. Nervous energy toward new people, places, and things.

Doss is an extremely loyal and loving dog but you must be committed to earning his trust and respect. He pushes boundaries until he knows that he can’t get away with it anymore. If you are a disciplined and committed person, then you might be the right human for Doss. 

If you’d like to meet Doss or if you have any questions about this boy, then please email the.underdogs.tail@gmail.com and fill out an application through www.apollosarc.org

home_environment_attributes.other_animals: Doss can get along with big dogs with proper introductions and close monitoring of behavior, but it not recommended right away. No small dogs or animals.

animal.description:
Hi guys I am back on the market, so to speak.  I am Kronos, I just turned 2 years old on May the 5th, 2020.  I am a Shepherd-hound mix but look like a gorgeous hound dog.  And in typical hound fashion, I sound like one too.  

I had a rough childhood having had 3 hernia repairs before I was 6 months old, but that just means my humans are my best friends.  I have a fat pocket on my belly that my mom calls my bump.  If I am the dog for you, and let’s face it I sure can be, my care includes checking my bump daily for any change in size or to see if it becomes hard.  I also need to be seen by a vet 2 times a year for a check on it along with ultrasounds as needed.  Mother Nature played a trick on me and didn’t give me all the stomach muscles I needed.  My hips are weak, I have moderate bilateral hip dysplasia and this will need to be monitored closely and will need pain meds on and off so routine vet visits are a must. But it's no big deal  (just means while I can jump on the couch, I can’t jump on the bed with you.  But a ramp or steps work great for that.  )  You don’t want to sleep with me? That’s fine I will gladly sleep on the couch.  

I am crated trained but I can be trusted to stay out of it, as I am not super crazy about being in one.  I am house broken and also pad trained.  

I am a proud graduate of the New Leash on Life program and I know sit, lay down, high five, stay, and come.  Put me on your left side on a leash and I will heel so well a child can walk me.  I don’t like cats at all and need to have a submissive doggie sibling that isn’t bigger than I am please.  

One last thing, I weigh 78 lbs, and look overweight but it’s just the lack of muscles.  

I adore children I need a respectful child that understands my needs.  I can be kinda clumsy and might knock a toddler over by accident .   

I'm so ready to find out who is going to be my forever family.  Could that be you??

Adoption Fee $150

Post for Lori M

animal.description:
BEAUTIFUL HONEY BUN IS LOOKING FOR A HEART TO STEAL AND A FUREVER HOME OF HER OWN!!!
Honey is an 8 old female mixed breed that lives up to her name! She loves all people and is as sweet as honey! She is a petite little girl at 46lbs. Judging by her condition when she entered the shelter Honey wasn't well cared for and was a puppy making machine!  She entered the shelter on 3/16/19 and was found as a stray wandering the streets of New Port Richey forced to fend for herself. I suspect, once Honey's owners were done with her and she couldn't provide them with any more puppies, she was left to survive on her own. This girl was super sick with pneumonia when we pulled her from the shelter. Her condition made you want to cry for her! She just looked completely miserable. But Honey is a fighter and she is fully recovered! The one thing that never changed through all of this is her love of people and her sweet and gentle disposition! Honey is spayed, microchipped and current on all her vaccines. She walks very well on a leash, and is a very easy going, lower energy girl. I suspect she had lived in a home before she was found, as she knows the comforts of a home, she knows come, sit and gently gives you both paws. She is also a big fan of treats! Her absolute favorite activity is being a velcro dog. She just wants a lap to lay in and to soak up all your love! Because I suspect Honey may have been forced to breed, she is not a fan of other dogs and would do best as the only pet in a home. She does well in her crate and is completely housebroken. If you are interested in adopting Honey Bun please contact me asap to schedule a meet and greet! I guarantee she will steal your heart like she does everyone she meets! You can call or text Danielle Nielson at 727.946.6428.

The name Popeye likely puts in mind large strong muscles, and while it does describe this big strong guy, Popeye is sweet as honey and has a heart of gold! Popeye has proved to be a delightful house guest and he is a smart cookie who knows Sit, Leave It, Off, Stay, Down, and Shake. He is completely housetrained and gets along wonderfully with humans of all ages. Popeye is a handsome, goofy, young, friendly, happy and playful guy with a lot of love to give. Popeye is a romantic guy, ready for long walks on the beach followed by a quiet snuggle session. Popeye is great on a leash and has an easy-going demeanor. He is also an athletic boy and would make a great hiking and running partner. He currently hikes regularly with our volunteers and is great at keeping pace! Popeye is ready for someone to take him home and love him forever. In the meantime, this 70-pound lover will continue to charm his way into our staff members' hearts!

animal.description:
Winston "Winnie" 
Long Haired Mini Dachshund mix
~6 years old
15 lbs

Winston is a spunky little guy that would do great in a home with other patient, small dogs and no children. He needs some help with social skills and trust, but is slowly warming up. He prefers to keep a regular schedule to avoid accidents in the house and food aggression issues. He likes to sleep under the blankets in true dachshund fashion and is starting to show interest in toys. 

This little boy has lots of love to give as long as you're patient enough to wait for him to feel comfortable. He was owner surrendered to the shelter for biting his owners, but we suspect he may have been abused there. 

* Friendly with all dogs, big or small! 
* Hasn’t had much exposure to cats but was indifferent when one was in a carrier next to him. 
* Not good with children
* Mix between both energetic and calm
* Cuddly and loves to snuggle
* Cautious of strangers, can take a while to warm up but once he does, he's loving
* Loves to go for car rides
* Likes to be held once he warms up to you
* Sleeps under the covers in his foster mom's bed 
* Likes to play with squeaky toys and stuffed animals, will play tug of war and chew on dog bones and toys but not your personal belongings!
* Has occasional accidents but does well if taken out on a schedule
* Knows how to Sit
* Although we cannot safely take away toys or food from Winnie, when presented with another option he will happily trade. So if he is caught chewing on/playing with something he shouldn’t be and we offer him a dog toy instead, he will take that with no fuss. 

Winston is neutered, up to date on vaccinations, and heartworm negative. He is current on heartworm/flea prevention. 

Apply to adopt at:
https://form.jotform.com/92846379021159

Note: Dogs are pack animals and do not do well away from other members of their pack. The adopter is the alpha member of the pack, and the dog or puppy needs as much one-on-one contact with the alpha as possible. For this reason, all Route 66 Rescue Inc. dogs are adopted to inside homes only. They must be on leash, or inside a secure fence when outside, and not left outside alone when no one is home. Invisible fencing does not qualify as protection since other animals and strangers have access to the dog. The dogs must be returned to Route 66 Rescue, Inc. if ever given up by the adopter. Thank you for understanding we want only the best for the dogs you give a forever home.

This is one of the sweetest girls you will ever meet.  She is a large, brindle, mixed breed girl.  I see a little Dane in her, but others don't see it.  She is quiet and respectful and loves people.  She would be better as an only dog although she does tolerate others.  We are looking for an adult home for Rosie.   She was born on 5/07/2017, and on 5/06/2020, she weighed 66.1 pounds.  Her adoption fee is $200.

Meet Waffle!

This man will capture your heart! 1 year old 40 pound sweet boy who needs a patient, loving quiet home.
He was rescued from a hoarding situation where he was living with 25 other dogs, and his living conditions were very sad.
So he needs to learn how to be a dog and to know he is safe and loved.
If your heart and home are big enough for a new best friend, Waffle is the one!

Interested in meeting Waffle? 

All Ma, Paws & Me Pet Rescue dogs are in homes with foster families; we do not have a shelter where dogs are available for daily viewing.

Our process is as follows:
1.  Review our policies and adoption radius  on our website: http://mapawsmepetrescue.com/adopt/
2.  Submit an application for review and approval;
3.  MPM Rescue reviews application and checks vet records and references;
4.  MPM foster contacts approved applicant(s) to arrange a home check and meeting with available dog(s);
5.   If there is a good fit, adoption is completed with a contract and fees (payable via check or cash).

The adoption fee is listed here: http://mapawsmepetrescue.com/adopt/

Dogs from Ma, Paws & Me Pet Rescue come with the following medical care already provided:
- Spay/Neuter surgery
- Age appropriate vaccinations
- Heartworm test (for dogs over 6mo) and treatment if positive
- Microchip
- Deworming
- Heartworm and Flea/Tick Preventative
- Any other necessary medical treatment as recommended by veterinarian

*Please note that the identified breed(s) are best guesses. We very rarely have information on our dogs' actual breeds since they often come to the shelters we work with as strays.*

animal.description:
Hugo Lionheart is the most handsome young boy, solid and athletic. His coat is red, and he has a subtle black face mask, with a white star on his chest. His left ear always flops to the right, which adds more character to his already endearing and expressive face!
 Hugo Lionheart loves love! 
He has such a fantastic personality: very friendly and affectionate, curious, playful, and extremely intelligent. Hugo is wonderfully eager to please, especially after a good play session and with some good treats.
This boy is friendly to everyone he meets, dogs and kids included, although has not been around cats.
Hugo needs walks and exercise like any big boy, but does love to settle in with a good chew toy wherever you are. A sturdy fenced yard would be a plus, but he is used to getting most of his exercise on a leash and does a lot of his playtime with toys in the house. He's a 'play hard, rest hard' kind of boy; by no means an endurance athlete. He will sploot flat on his belly wherever his is when he needs a break 
Regular walks and play will be key to his success as a good house companion. He does well with routine and structure and needs a home that will provide regular quiet time in his kennel, where he is calm and content. Leash manners are mostly good, and he is highly motivated by treats.
Hugo is a very strong chewer and needs toys designed for his kind of play . He loves his food and toys, but is gentle and willing to give them up to his person without complaint. However, his ultra expressive eyebrows will certainly convince you to give his toys right back!
He doesn't seem to understand why his size might be an obstacle to being a lapdog, and enjoys a good full body hug. As Hugo could easily knock someone over, we only allow laps and hugs on invite :). 
Hugo prefers to be with his people, but does very well in his crate without anxiety for 4-5 hours at a time. He rarely barks, but sometimes kind of talks to get your attention.
 Hugo Lionheart came from a local shelter.
 Read more about Hugo Lionheart on the Independent Animal Rescue website at https://animalrescue.net/dogs/d-20-051/.

animal.description:
Hello! My name is Hershey! I am a potty trained cur mix born in February 2020, I weigh about 30lbs right now. 
Me and my brother were found as strays and were super timid when I first met my foster mom. It didn’t take long for me to come out of my shell though. I love to run around outside and play with my brother. I get along well with my fur foster brother, he is only 8lbs though so I sometimes forget I am bigger and stronger than him. I just want to give him kisses all the time. Same with kids - love to kiss and snuggle them too! I’m not sure what a cat is, but it sounds like I would want to play with one! 
I like to sleep in my kennel, but my foster mom has let me have sleepovers in her bed and I curl up next to her all night. I and doing so well with house training, soooo very close to 100%
 I love to stand by my foster mom’s feet when she cooks, I keep hoping she will drop something! I love to run around and play outside, but I also love to curl up next to her with a toy on the couch. My foster mom is teaching me how to “sit” and tells me I am such a good boy! She smothers me with kisses all the time and she tells me I am as sweet as a hershey bar! I am utd on my vaccines and will be neutered in October. I would love to show you what a good boy I am!

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our dogs are healthy, spayed/neutered, vaccinated and on heartworm preventative. They live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. animal.description: Cesar is a 4.5 year old male mixed breed. He weighs 52 pounds. He is an active, busy boy. From having Cesar in the office we have learned that Cesar is a resource guarder. This means that he can be possessive of both treats and toys with humans. He gives plenty of appropriate warnings to let you know that he isn't fond of sharing. Cesar was transferred from a county facility so we do not have information about his previous household. Cesar has had some positive dog interactions at the shelter and some negative dog interactions at the shelter. We do not know if the resource guarding issue with treats and toys extends to his dog friends as we have not introduced toys during any dog interactions. We would definitely recommend a meet and greet with any resident dogs. At the shelter Cesar met a kitten, somewhat accidentally, and he was extremely rude. At this time we don't believe Cesar would do well living with cats. We have no information on how Cesar behaves around children. However, due to Cesar's resource guarding we would recommend him only with older children that are able to read and respect Cesar's communication about sharing (or rather not sharing) his toys and treats. We always recommend a meet and greet with any children in the household or children that visit often, such as grandkids. From Cesar's time in the office we have also learned that he can easily clear a baby gate in one hop. Please call for more information or to make an appointment to meet Cesar. (Updated 1/30/21).

animal.description:
A LITTLE BIT ABOUT ME
5/8/20 HELLO, MY NAME IS JACK! 

I AM APPROXIMATELY  3 YEARS OLD AND NEED TO FIND A FOREVER HOME.

I am looking for someone with a big heart, single dog home, and willing to foster or adopt me, a big sweet boy, I have had a horrible past life where I roamed stray for months, lived in an abandoned junk filled trailer, and I have a skin injury from scalding it appears. I also was heartworm positive and had to be treated for this.  I was in a wonderful foster home for almost a year when I got into a scuffle with one of my foster siblings over food and when the foster mom tried to break it up, I bit onto her arm. I do well with other dogs except for the food issue based on my previous life. I am begging for someone to give me a chance! 
From my rescuers: We are devastated for Jack as he is such a loving dog. Please give him a chance!
 I AM ALSO HOUSEBROKEN AND CRATE TRAINED. 

I ALSO DO WELL ON CAR RIDES BUT WILL NEED SOME TRAINING FOR WALKING WELL ON A LEASH AS I AM A STRONG AND BIG BOY. A FENCED IN YARD IS REQUIRED..

I HAVE ALL OF MY VET WORK DONE, INCLUDING NEUTERING, MICROCHIPPED, HEARTWORM TESTED AND ON MONTHLY PREVENTION,AND ALL SHOTS UP TO DATE. 

PLEASE FILL OUT AN APPLICATION IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN ME AND I HOPE TO MEET YOU SOON!
HERE IS SOME MORE YOU NEED TO KNOW IF INTERESTED IN ADOPTING ME! 
Click here to complete our adoption application and please email to Kim at lovemelovemydogs2004@indy.rr.com: GRACIE'S HEART OF GOLD ADOPTION APPLICATION GRACIE'S HEART OF GOLD REQUIRES ONGOING PROPER VETERINARY CARE FOR ALL ANIMALS ADOPTED TO INCLUDE HEARTWORM MEDICATIONS, FLEA MEDICATIONS, AND YEARLY VACCINATIONS. GRACIES HEART OF GOLD DOES NOT SHIP OUR DOGS - WE REQUIRE A FACE TO FACE MEETING. WE ALSO DO NOT ADOPT OUR DOGS AS GIFTS UNLESS THE RECIPIENT MEETS WITH THE DOG PRIOR TO ADOPTION. MY ADOPTION FEE IS: $150. THESE FEES HELP KEEP THE RESCUE GOING. PLEASE READ MORE! Adoption fees average $150-$400. This fee varies per animal based on additional vet care required to save them. Due to the rising costs of veterinary care, premium holistic dog food, gasoline prices, and boarding fees, which are paid for out of our own pockets, we recently were forced to raise our fees. We are not funded by anyone - adoption fees help to offset only a part of our cost of getting the dog ready for adoption. All dogs > 6 months are vetted, up to date on vaccinations, spayed/neutered, microchipped, heartworm tested, wormed and have a goody starter bag. Puppies
